{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"18646","heading":"Nuclear physics","label":"18646 Nuclear physics","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch161/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2022— amended section generally. Prior to amendment, text was comprised of subsec. (a) of which read as follows: “The Director—Pub. L. 117–167section 308 of Pub. L. 115–246“(1) may carry out a program for the production of isotopes, including the development of techniques to produce isotopes, that the Secretary determines are needed for research, medical, industrial, or related purposes; and“(2) shall ensure that isotope production activities carried out under the program under this paragraph do not compete with private industry unless the Director determines that critical national interests require the involvement of the Federal Government.”Prior to amendment, also contained subsec. (b) which amended .section 308 of Pub. L. 115–246section 16321 of this title"],"amendments":["Amendments2022— amended section generally. Prior to amendment, text was comprised of subsec. (a) of which read as follows: “The Director—Pub. L. 117–167section 308 of Pub. L. 115–246“(1) may carry out a program for the production of isotopes, including the development of techniques to produce isotopes, that the Secretary determines are needed for research, medical, industrial, or related purposes; and“(2) shall ensure that isotope production activities carried out under the program under this paragraph do not compete with private industry unless the Director determines that critical national interests require the involvement of the Federal Government.”Prior to amendment, also contained subsec. (b) which amended .section 308 of Pub. L. 115–246section 16321 of this title"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Program","label":"a Program","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"As part of the activities authorized under , the Director shall carry out a research program, and support relevant facilities, to discover and understand various forms of nuclear matter.section 7139 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Electron Ion Collider","label":"b Electron Ion Collider","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall support construction of an Electron Ion Collider as described in the 2015 Long Range Plan of the Nuclear Science Advisory Committee and the report from the National Academies of Science, Engineering, and Medicine entitled “An Assessment of U.S.-Based Electron-Ion Collider Science”, in order to measure the internal structure of the proton and the nucleus and answer fundamental questions about the nature of visible matter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Facility capability","label":"2 Facility capability","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"at least 70 percent polarized beams of electrons and light ions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ion beams from deuterium to the heaviest stable nuclei;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"variable center of mass energy from 20 to 140 GeV;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"high collision luminosity of 10cms; and33–34-2-1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the possibility of more than 1 interaction region.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Start of operations","label":"3 Start of operations","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall, subject to the availability of appropriations, ensure that the start of full operations of the facility under this subsection occurs before .December 31, 2030","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Funding","label":"4 Funding","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$90,000,000 for fiscal year 2023;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18646/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18646%2Fb%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$181,000,000 for fiscal year 2024;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"sub